At 08:36 AM 5/27/2010, airic wrote...
>They tend to get warm, and then cause the ignition system to die, but 
>then after they cool off they go back to working for awhile.

Yep. Mine did exactly that until I put a ballast resistor on the coil 
(a Brazilian Bosch Blue). I'm using a 1.1 ohm, and haven't had any 
ignition problems since adding it. T4 engine w/FI.
